+<h3>Features<a class="headerlink" href="#features" title="Permalink to this heading"></a></h3>
 <ul class="simple">
 <li><p>Generates schematic part libraries for KiCad from CSV/text/Excel files.</p></li>
 <li><p>Converts lists of pins in a file into a multi-unit schematic part symbol.</p></li>
 <li><p>Converts multiple files stored in .zip archives.</p></li>
 <li><p>Each row of the file lists the number, name, type, style, unit and side of a pin.</p></li>
 <li><p>Pins on a unit with the same name (e.g., GND) can be placed at the same location
 so they can all be tied to the same net with a single connection.</p></li>
 <li><p>Also includes <code class="docutils literal notranslate"><span class="pre">kilib2csv</span></code> for converting schematic part libraries into
 CSV files suitable for input to KiPart.</p></li>
 </ul>
